
Overview of noun altogether

The noun altogether has 1 sense (no senses from tagged texts)
                                    
1. raw, altogether, birthday suit -- (informal terms for nakedness; "in the raw"; "in the altogether"; "in his birthday suit")

Overview of adv altogether

The adv altogether has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (11) wholly, entirely, completely, totally, all, altogether, whole -- (to a complete degree or to the full or entire extent (`whole' is often used informally for `wholly'); "he was wholly convinced"; "entirely satisfied with the meal"; "it was completely different from what we expected"; "was completely at fault"; "a totally new situation"; "the directions were all wrong"; "it was not altogether her fault"; "an altogether new approach"; "a whole new idea")
2. (1) altogether, all told, in all -- (with everything included or counted; "altogether he earns close to a million dollars")
3. all in all, on the whole, altogether, tout ensemble -- (with everything considered (and neglecting details); "altogether, I'm sorry it happened"; "all in all, it's not so bad")
